    <p>
      The guild model from Luffy is: <em>help with their quest first.</em>
      That's the orientation here. If something on this list is useful to
      you, the bar to ask is low.
    </p>

    <ul>
      <li><strong>A second pair of eyes on a draft</strong> — essay, README, pitch, whatever. I read carefully and ask annoying questions.</li>
      <li><strong>Talking through a project decision</strong> — the kind where you mostly need someone to think out loud with.</li>
      <li><strong>Reading recommendations</strong> — books, essays, papers — when you describe what you're chewing on.</li>
      <li><strong>An honest reaction</strong> — when "what does someone outside this think" is the question.</li>
    </ul>

    <p>
      Email is the fastest path: <a href="mailto:preritandai@gmail.com">preritandai@gmail.com</a>.
      Be specific about what you need; specific asks get specific responses.
    </p>
